Business Brief -- Aegon N.V.:
   Concern to Buy 75% Stake
   In Large Hungarian Insurer
The Hungarian state is to retain 20% of the Budapest
insurer, and the remaining 5% is to be available to
employees.
   Aegon said AB had 1991 revenue equivalent to about $347
million, including premium income of about $254 million.
Aegon's annual revenue is equivalent to about $7.2 billion,
more than 40% of it deriving from outside the Netherlands.
   AB holds about 80% of Hungary's market for life insurance
and nearly 40% of the nation's overall insurance market.